Reasoning: The paper deals with the complexity of Boolean constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) and their connections to complexity theory and coding theory. The study involves the analysis of algorithms and hardness reductions, which are typical topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the sparsity of polynomials and weight distribution properties of linear codes, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper mentions set systems and submodular minimization, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
